Reasoning: 
1. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper deals with logic programming languages and handling incomplete information, which are topics commonly studied in the field of AI. 
2. cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) - The paper presents an extended definition of splitting sets and an extension of the splitting set theorem, which are concepts related to logic in computer science. 
3. cs.PL (Programming Languages) - The paper deals with logic programming languages and their extensions, which is a topic studied in the field of programming languages. 
4. cs.CL (Computation and Language) - The paper deals with the problem of answering queries, which is a topic studied in the field of natural language processing. 
5. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper deals with epistemic logic programs, which are used in the field of cryptography and security for reasoning about knowledge and belief.
